# agentfiles-scan.sh deny-list (example / committed).
#
# This file ships generic placeholder tokens only. To scan for your own
# organization's real internal identifiers (hostnames, org names, emails,
# usernames, etc.), copy this file to `denylist.local` in this same
# directory and add your real tokens there, one per line.
#
# `denylist.local` is gitignored and will never be committed. The scanner
# prefers it automatically when present (see agentfiles-scan.sh), falling
# back to this example file otherwise. You can also point at an arbitrary
# file via the AF_DENYLIST environment variable.
#
# Blank lines and lines starting with # are ignored. Remaining lines are
# treated as extended-regex (ERE) alternatives, so escape regex metachars
# (e.g. `\.`) if you want a literal match.
example-internal-hostname
example-org-name
noreply@example.invalid
